Description: Rim and neck sherd of East Greek, possibly South Ionian, pottery trefoil-mouthed oinochoe; interior: glazed black at top of sherd, reserved below; exterior: glazed black; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 221)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 661, no. 182)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.041)
